args: Gather round, one and all, for\nour pulse-pounding, spooktastic\nHalloween Costume Contest!
The contestant with the most Halloween-y\ncostume'll be named the victor, and all\nthe rest'll be sent straight to the dungeons.
Your judges today are of course myself,\n＂Always Dressed for Halloween＂ Annelie,\naaand...
Me, ＂Can't Turn Down a Job＂ Vice.\n...Hold on, who's the wise guy?!
Just stick to the script! *ahem*\nHere comes our first contestant!
He's the king of more than just costumes,\nand he's probably called you a vassal\nat some point—iiit's Xandeeer!
Ha HA! Or, er, ho HO! I am Saint Starfall!\nWho would like a present from the king\nhimself?
Looks like this king missed the memo;\nI'm not seein' a lick of Halloween flavor.\nSmells like disqualification to me!
Sorry about that folks. I'm sure our NEXT\ncontestant won't make the same mistake,\nright, Annelie?

Ab-so-lutely. And here she comes now!
Put your hands together for the mom of
the Halidom, a girl with one heckuva
wand arm—Cleooo!
Is this all right?\nIt feels a bit out of season.
It's a knockout number, no doubt there—\nbut I'm not getting much ＂Halloween.＂
Ah, I have this as well.
Nothing Halloween-y about any of\nthose either. But, er, how come\nyou have so many outfits?
Oh, a certain princess has been sending\nthem quite frequently of late.
How about that, folks? A mom who\nstill gets an allowance! Ha ha!
That explains it. But you're still missing\nthe theme, so... Dungeon!
And after I brought all those\ncostuuuuuuuumes!

Let's move on to contestant number three.
He loves long walks in the moonlight,
and he's got a knack for scaring kids.
Give it up for...a suit of armor?
Hang on, I know who this is!
Duh, it's Berserker. And he's just in his\nnormal outfit! Does no one around here\nunderstand the word ＂costume＂?!
Deep breaths. Come on, you can do this!\nLeft foot, right foot, l-left foot...
Hold on a tick... Is that little Ricardt\nin there?

You're okay. You're okay! Nothing can hurt
you with this armor on. Not even these
copious blood stains... EYAAAAAAGH!
BLOOOOOOOD!
Er... On to the next contestant, I guess.
Is it still a costume if you're just\nwearing someone else's clothes?\nGuess we'll never know!

Our next contestant is no stranger to
subterfuge, and if you mess with her,
she'll give you the horns.
Here cooomes Aoi!
I don't know what I'm looking at,\nbut it's not a costume.
Sure it is! You just need to think\noutside the box. Here's another\none: ＂Raging Ninja!＂
Aoi, we've fought together. I know your\nninja arts when I see them. Now get OUT!
*sigh* If I don't see an actual Halloween\ncostume soon, I'm just gonna walk.

Sounds like expectations are high for
contestant number five! And this figure
is completely shrouded in mystery...
Even WE'RE in the dark!
Right. So what's your costume, then?
I'm starting to question if costumes\neven exist.
Stay with me, we're almost done!
The next contestant is our last of the day,\nfolks!
Please have a costume, please have\na costume...

Ooo, looks like your prayers have been
answered, Vice! Mixing old-school
Halloween vibes with a rustic aesthetic,
here comes the Pumpking!
THIS is what I've been waiting for!
I totally feel you. The pumpkin theme is\nexecuted to perfection, and the giant\nlollipop is a master stroke.
Yep! And not just because they're\nthe only one left, no sir!
Give it up one more time for our winner,\nthe true embodiment of Halloween—the\nPumpking, everybody!
Oh! They say they're going to work\nhard to live up to this honor, and not\nlose out to anyone, fiend or otherwise.
That brings our Halloween Costume\nContest to a close, folks. I've been Vice,\nyour ＂Assassin Stuck in the Kitchen.＂
Don't forget me! Annelie, ＂Master of Tricks\nAND Treats.＂ See ya!
Hey, by the way, who's actually in\nthat costume?
